38
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:29,625
Whoa, you think it might
be the one from the curse?

39
00:03:29,708 --> 00:03:31,625
Sometimes, and I know
how this sounds,

40
00:03:31,708 --> 00:03:33,750
but I get this feeling that
maybe the old legends

41
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:35,791
and folk tales are
real, you know?

42
00:03:35,875 --> 00:03:37,666
How are you this excited?

43
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,541
[YUKI] Like, there might be
an entrance that takes you

44
00:03:39,625 --> 00:03:41,250
to some alternate
universe that only opens

45
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:42,750
once every few hundred years!

46
00:03:42,833 --> 00:03:45,500
Wait a minute. Where are
you getting this from?

47
00:03:45,583 --> 00:03:47,416
It's fascinating stuff, right?

48
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:50,583
It was in a book I read by
Doctor Kodai Somethin'-or-Other.

49
00:03:50,666 --> 00:03:54,375
--Uh. Boss? Uh, hello?
--[dial tone]

50
00:04:03,291 --> 00:04:05,083
It's fairly simple, really.

51
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:07,833
You'll experience the
same events over again.

52
00:04:07,916 --> 00:04:09,916
Only this time everything
is going to play out

53
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,125
slightly different than before.

54
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:16,583
[bell rings]

55
00:04:16,666 --> 00:04:17,708
