63
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:35,833
Heh. And I was reduced to
waiting around at home.

64
00:04:35,916 --> 00:04:39,291
Lately, I've been keeping
to the indoors at night.

65
00:04:39,375 --> 00:04:41,791
Scared of the curse,
guess you could say.

66
00:04:41,875 --> 00:04:43,833
[AYUMI]
Oh, come on, you are not!

67
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,416
[AYUMI laughs]

68
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:49,000
Laugh all you want, but I have
no plans to be the third victim!

69
00:04:49,083 --> 00:04:50,333
[TAKUYA grunts]

70
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:56,541
[gasps]

71
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:00,875
[gasps]

72
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:08,583
[KANNA]
The teacher's not here.

73
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:20,375
[gasping]

74
00:05:21,166 --> 00:05:23,333
Wait, why's this here?

75
00:05:23,416 --> 00:05:24,958
Excuse me.

76
00:05:25,041 --> 00:05:27,166
[MIO] So, you've finally
revealed your true nature!

77
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:28,541
What're you talking about?

78
00:05:28,625 --> 00:05:30,208
[MIO] Here I thought
you were just a pervert,

79
00:05:30,291 --> 00:05:31,583
but you're a mega-pervert!

80
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:34,416
I'm gonna stop you there.
Believe me, I'm the most

81
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,833
straight-laced, buttoned-down
dude you'll ever meet.

82
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:38,708
Are you being serious right now?

83
00:05:38,791 --> 00:05:41,833
You're literally touching
someone's panties!

84
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:44,125
Where the heck is
Ms. Eriko, anyway?

85
00:05:44,208 --> 00:05:45,458
Don't ask me.

86
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:47,625
[MIO] I mean, her clothes
are right there. Why?

87
00:05:47,708 --> 00:05:49,208
How should I know?

88
00:05:49,291 --> 00:05:51,875
Maybe the lucky thing finally
shed her cocoon and flew off.

89
00:05:51,958 --> 00:05:53,791
[MIO]
She's not a freaking butterfly!

90
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:55,208
And could you please
stop being gross

91
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:57,833
and put the panties down
while you talk to me?

92
00:05:57,916 --> 00:06:00,916
Fine! Bye!

93
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,250
[MIO]
Where do you think you're going?

94
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:07,125
[MITSUKI]
Takuya.

95
00:06:07,208 --> 00:06:07,958
Uh.

96
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:09,958
I need to talk to you.

97
00:06:13,166 --> 00:06:17,583
How has Ryuzoji seemed to you?
Notice any changes lately?

98
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:19,458
What type of changes?

99
00:06:19,541 --> 00:06:24,166
For example, this is small, but
he used to criticize smoking,

100
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:27,458
and now he's started
smoking cigars.

101
00:06:27,541 --> 00:06:29,541
[TAKUYA] People pick up
bad habits all the time.

102
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:31,208
What's the big deal?

103
00:06:31,291 --> 00:06:32,666
It's not just that.

104
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:35,458
His mother actually came
to me about this first.

105
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:37,458
[TAKUYA]
"Please, marry my lonely son?"

106
00:06:37,541 --> 00:06:39,208
Stop, don't joke.

107
00:06:39,291 --> 00:06:40,708
[TAKUYA]
Ha, ha. Sorry.

108
00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:44,500
She could see it. And then
I started to notice it, too.

109
00:06:44,583 --> 00:06:47,000
Subtle changes in his character.

110
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:49,708
There's no denying
that he's different.

111
00:06:49,791 --> 00:06:51,125
You know what?

112
00:06:51,208 --> 00:06:54,375
There's been something bugging
me about Ryuzoji, too.

113
00:06:54,458 --> 00:06:58,083
Have you noticed him talking
to anyone strange lately?

114
00:06:58,166 --> 00:06:59,666
[MITSUKI]
Yes. I have.

115
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:01,625
[TAKUYA] There's this one
self-proclaimed journalist

116
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:04,208
named Kaori Asakura
to be careful of.

117
00:07:04,291 --> 00:07:06,166
There's another one besides her.

118
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:08,750
He's actually hired
a detective now.

119
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:10,583
[grunts, gasps]

120
00:07:10,666 --> 00:07:11,666
[groaning]

121
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:12,958
[TAKUYA]
What's wrong?

122
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,041
[MITSUKI sighs]

123
00:07:17,125 --> 00:07:18,166
[TAKUYA]
You okay?

124
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:20,708
Yeah. It's just a migraine.

125
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:22,708
[TAKUYA] I talked to
Ryuzoji this morning,

126
00:07:22,791 --> 00:07:24,583
and something felt off.

127
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:26,333
Wow, you too?

128
00:07:26,416 --> 00:07:29,750
One thing, in particular,
when he talked about the curse.

129
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:33,750
Laugh all you want, but I have
no plans to be the third victim.

130
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,500
He said the third?

131
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:37,250
Yep, and as far as I know,

132
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:39,750
the news has only
reported one victim.

133
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:42,000
Strange, what are we
supposed to make of that?

134
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:45,375
Hard to say, but it didn't
feel like he misspoke.

135
00:07:45,458 --> 00:07:47,291
I'm taking my dad's
research materials

136
00:07:47,375 --> 00:07:49,083
to Ryuzoji's house today.

137
00:07:49,166 --> 00:07:51,541
I'll use the opportunity
to check on him.

138
00:07:51,625 --> 00:07:53,750
I appreciate that.
There was no one

139
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:57,208
